The WolfRiders have settled into their new Holt in the Forbidden Grove. The tumult of the Quest is behind them, and new life has come to the tribe. All is peaceful... until Aroree, fugitive Glider from Blue Mountain kidnaps a WolfRider child. The elves must once again confront Winnowill and her schemes—but first they must get through the humans who worship the evil temptress!
name: Siege at Blue Mountain

description: Rayek. To followers of ElfQuest the name speaks of pride, magic and thwarted ambition. Why is the black-haired Sun Villager the way her is? What drives him to become the rogue elf who issues the final challenge to his only rival?
name: Rogue's Challenge

description:
This is the action packed, mystical tale of a space faring centorg and his journey of self-discovery. Long before he helped Queen Jatarri to rid the planet Pratkill of the dreaded Spigmodite Plaue (in Dark One's highly acclaimed ANIMAL MYSTIC series), Klor was a barbaric, arrogant killer. But that all changed when the enigmatic Father Kroy sets Klor on the path toward inner power!

Klor must battle not only his personal demons, but also Father Kroy's rogue pupil, Mirgin—a vile centorg bent on destroying the Muishaa Order and overrunning the galaxy with the shaggy hordes of darkness. Only Klor has the power to stop him, but can he realize this before is't too late?
name: TPB

description:
Does the Tenth herald the end of mankind—or its last hope for survival?

Esperanza del Toro, whose telekinetic powers have marked her as an outcast all of her young life, shares a psychic bond with former CIA operative Victor de Leon—the tenth victim of a madman's genetic experiments that turned him into a quasi-vampire and gave him enormous strength. Together, with Esperanza's friend Zorina Fine, their search for a cure to Victor's condition brings them into conflict with super-powered assassins and the evil minions of Rhazes Darkk—the madman—who seeks to remake humanity in his own alien image!

Collected here for the first time are the first five issue is Tony Daniel's acclaimed series The Tenth, which featured another of his breakout characters, the deadly Russian cyborg, Adrenalynn!
name: TPB
